@startuml sequence_error_handling
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Plugin Error Handling — Fail-Safe Loading

participant "PluginLoader" as Loader
participant "PluginLoadContext" as LoadCtx
participant "PluginCommandRegistrar" as Registrar
participant "ICliPlugin" as Plugin
participant "RootCommand" as Root
participant "ILogger" as Log

== Scenario 1: Assembly Load Failure ==

Loader -> LoadCtx : LoadFromAssemblyPath(\n  "plugins/corrupt/Bad.dll")

LoadCtx --> Loader : <<throws>>\nBadImageFormatException

Loader -> Log : LogWarning(\n  "Failed to load plugin: {path}\n  Error: {message}")

note right of Loader
    Plugin is skipped.
    Other plugins continue loading.
end note

== Scenario 2: No ICliPlugin Types ==

Loader -> LoadCtx : LoadFromAssemblyPath(\n  "plugins/lib/Utility.dll")
LoadCtx --> Loader : Assembly (loaded OK)

Loader -> Loader : Scan types for ICliPlugin
Loader -> Loader : No matching types found

Loader -> Log : LogWarning(\n  "No ICliPlugin types in: {path}")

== Scenario 3: CreateCommand Throws ==

Registrar -> Plugin : CreateCommand(serviceProvider)
Plugin --> Registrar : <<throws>>\nInvalidOperationException(\n  "Missing config file")

Registrar -> Log : LogWarning(\n  "Plugin '{name}' failed to\n  create command: {message}")

Registrar -> Registrar : Create fallback command:\n  name = plugin.Name\n  handler prints error

Registrar -> Root : AddCommand(fallbackCommand)

note right of Root
    User sees the command in --help
    but gets a clear error message
    if they try to invoke it.
end note

@enduml
